      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "As noted in the 1990 Institute of Medicine report, \"the majority of alcohol-related morbidity stems not from the alcohol-dependent patient, but from the patient that simply drinks too much from time to time.\"  Defining safe drinking limits allows the provider to address this issue in an initial brief counseling intervention without having to label the patient as an alcoholic or nonalcoholic."
